PLANE
  List your planes in a human-readable table.

SYNTAX
  plane [<uid-spec>][?realm=N][&type=X]
  pln   [<uid-spec>][?realm=N][&type=X]

DESCRIPTION
  Displays a table of planes you own.  With no argument shows all
  your planes.

  <uid-spec>  - a uid ("5"), a uid range ("0-5"), a comma list, "*"
                for all, "~" for planes with no wing assigned, or a
                single letter naming a wing (see 'info wingadd').
                Same grammar 'fly'/'bomb'/'recon' accept -- note that
                "#N" here means uid N (not a realm), same as those
                commands.

  Two optional filters can be appended after '?' (and combined with
  '&'), matching the sector-spec '?condition' convention (info realm):

    ?realm=N    - only planes currently within realm N's bounding box
                  (see 'info realm' to define realms; unlike sector
                  specs, planes use ?realm=N rather than #N, since #N
                  already means "uid N" for plane/ship/land specs)
    ?type=X     - only planes of type X -- matches the short type
                  code shown in 'show plane' (e.g. "f35") or a
                  case-insensitive substring of the full name (e.g.
                  "raptor" matches "F-22 Raptor")

  Column meanings:
    pln#        - plane uid
    plane type  - name of plane type (bomber, fighter, etc.)
    x,y         - current location (relative to your capital)
    wg          - wing letter (~ means not assigned to a wing)
    eff         - efficiency 0-100%.  Builds up over time in an
                  owned, non-offline airfield with lcm/hcm on hand
    mob         - mobility points
    tech        - tech level the plane was built at
    mission     - current mission code (0 = none)
    range       - maximum range in sectors

EXAMPLE
  plane *                    all your planes
  pln 0                      plane number 0 only
  pln 0-5                    planes 0 through 5
  plane *?realm=2            all planes within realm 2
  plane *?type=f35           all F-35s, wherever they are
  plane *?realm=2&type=f35   F-35s within realm 2 only

